Create a Salesforce CRM Data Stream

Create a data stream to begin the flow of data from a Salesforce CRM data source.

If the objects selected for the data stream support change events, the selections are added to a Change Data Capture standard channel named DataCloudEntities. Make sure you don't modify the selections for this standard channel in Metadata API or Tooling API. Updating the channel selections using the API can result in unexpected synchronizations of Salesforce objects that weren't intended by the Data Cloud administrator. For more information about Change Data Capture channels, see Change Data Capture.
The Event object fields: Attendees, Email, and Phone aren’t supported because the value for these fields is retrieved from other objects.
For your data stream to be processed using the streaming process, the object must be included in the list of objects that support change events, see StandardObjectNameChangeEvent.
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab and click New.
Select the Salesforce CRM data source and click Next.
To create your data stream, select a Salesforce org.
If you have only one Salesforce org connected to Data Cloud, it’s selected by default.
Select the All Objects tab and click Next.
Select the Salesforce Object that you want to include in the data stream and click Next.
Review the fields to include in your data stream and click Next.
All fields are preselected by default. The number of fields available for the object is shown in parentheses.
In the Header Label, deselect the fields not required for your data stream.
If needed, add these formula fields and then click Next.
Field Label—The display name for a data stream field.
Field API Name—The programmatic reference for a data stream field.
Formula Return Type—The data type corresponding to the new field. The options are number, text, and date.
Enter the deployment details.
The data stream name defaults to the object label and the alias that’s provided when setting up connection to a Salesforce CRM org. Connections that were created before the alias option was available use the object label and Salesforce org ID for the data stream name. You can change the name of a data stream.
The refresh and frequency are set by default. For more information, see Data Stream Schedule in Data Cloud.
Click Deploy.
Your Salesforce CRM data stream is now created.

To create more data streams, repeat these steps.

Ingestion Errors and Refresh Failures
Keep these considerations in mind when creating a Salesforce CRM data stream.
Unsupported Objects and Object Types in CRM Data Streams
When you create a Salesforce CRM data stream, the CRM connector doesn’t support ingestion of all objects types and objects from the connected CRM orgs. Consider these restrictions when you create a Salesforce CRM data stream.
Mapping for DateTime, Date, and Boolean Objects
The Salesforce CRM connector maps the objects DateTime, Date, and Boolean based on the object and field type.
